  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide Relief to 5000 Families in Typhoon Bopha</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Typhoon Bopha has devastated communities across the Mindanao region of the Philippines; 300 people have perished and over 200,000 are in evacuation centers. Asia America Initiative in partnership with local officials, community groups, military logistics teams and youth volunteers is conducting ongoing relief in the most hard to reach areas where roads and bridges are destroyed.  Help us provide food, medicine, hygiene, blankets for 5,000 families with close to 15,000 infants and children.</narrative>
  </description>
